	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Congrats! I have no idea where I would start in writing an emulator, and you've managed to keep one alive for 20 years, that's crazy! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br />So, I see no replies to this topic yet, so I'll say what was on my mind. Honestly, I kind of feel like bundling the emulator download with parallel data could be something the users wouldn't really want (a bigger download when all they want is the emulator).<br />For an emulator I can't really think of anything better for a gift than a free game. Since you're willing to part with the bandwidth required to upload extra things, why not make a built-in option in the emulator to download from a select list of homebrew games? Then people here could give the ok for you to include their homebrews on the list.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


